HEADWORD: Fustet
<hw>Fus"tet</hw> <pr>(f⟦ucr⟧s"t⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fustet</ets> (cf. Sp. & Pg. <ets>fustete</ets>), LL.
<ets>fustetus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>fustis</ets> stick, in LL., tree, See
<er>1st Fust</er>, and cf. <er>Fustic</er>.]</ety> <def>The wood of the
<spn>Rhus Cotinus</spn> or <prodby>Venice sumach</prodby>, a shrub of
Southern Europe, which yields a fine orange color, which, however, is
not durable without a mordant.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

